         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">29/3/81 ¶  ¶ It is a strange coincidence, dear Mr Fawcett, that I just thought of writing to you, when your very kind and thoughtful letter arrived. The last 5 or 6 months I had so much extrawork for ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.03.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Charles<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fawcett</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Parkes correspondence, ML A925, pp. 240-6, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/3/81</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is a strange coincidence, dear Mr Fawcett, that I just thought of writing to you, when your very kind and thoughtful letter arrived. The last 5 or 6 months I had so much extrawork for the Exhibition,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1880-1.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that I could give no attention to even official Departmental matters, unless of urgency, and thus my correspondence got altogether into arrear.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>But if I did not write, I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">did</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>think of you, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">often too</hi>
               </seg>, as I was daily reminded of your generous interest in the N.SW. edition of the select plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B81.01.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>To day I learn, that Sir Henry Parkes has kindly acted on your disinterested suggestion, and 100 copies of the work are forwarded to me, after I had already some presentation copies before. This gracious gift enables me to place the book<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">on behalf</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">of the</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">N.S.W.</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Government</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>into many Libraries abroad.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sorry, you cannot come to the Exhibition,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>altho', after the previous grand display in Sydney,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Sydney, 1879.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the worlds fair here has perhaps not so much attraction, as otherwise would have been the case. Had you come, I would have shown you every attention, altho' unfortunately I have not even a room for a friend in the small temporary dwelling,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which I occupy for my<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">O</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ffice</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>work and where actually my bedroom is my writing place.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir Joseph Hooker has just figured the Wistaria (Milletia<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Millettia?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>megasperma in the bot Magazine,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1865-1904), vol. 107, t. 6541 (issued 1 February 1881).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as it flowered this year for the first time in Kew. The one with smaller fruits (seeds), of which we never got the flowers yet, will probably remain unattainable until<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>get back into your favorite haunts of the Richmond River<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>When you see Sir Henry Parkes, kindly thank the honorable Gentleman for his generosity anew shown.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is certainly conducive to diseminating knowledge on rural objects, if the work, as suggested by you is placed into every Mechanics Institute &amp; free Library in New South Wales and if the Editors of all the Newspapers of your colony receive it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will be to me great pleasure to revise your list of the plants of the Richmond-River, which to gather you spent so much time and exertions. Major Richards deserves much credit for the quick &amp; splendid manner in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which he brought out the new edition. Trusting, dear Mr Fawcett, that you are happy and well, I remain your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Can I do anything for you?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Wistaria megasperma</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Milletia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>megasperma</p>
         </div>
